article.headline: Prairie View 75, Alabama State 72
article.story: PRAIRIE VIEW, Texas (AP) -- Oscar Thompson scored a game-high 24 points to lead Prairie View A&M to a 75-72 win over Alabama State on Monday night. Prairie View A&M (5-22, 2-14 Southwestern Athletic Conference) trailed 37-25 at halftime but came back to score 50 points in the second half. Jeremy Wiley had 15 points for the Panthers and Chris Gaines had 13. Dominique Sharpe added 10 points and had a game-high seven rebounds. Andrew Hayles led Alabama State (11-16, 9-7) with 17 points and shot 3-of-7 from 3-point range. LaMarquis Blake added 11 points for the Hornets. The Panthers shot 44 percent from the field and the Hornets shot 49 percent.
